Events that occurred on 9 May.

content.title: On Earth
content.content:
1907 - J.R.R. Tolkien receives the book Dictionary in Englysshe and Welshe.
1921 - Voice actor Brian Haines is born.
1957 - J.R.R. Tolkien writes Letter 197.
1961 - J.R.R. Tolkien writes a letter to Mr. Hart.
1967 - J.R.R. Tolkien writes a letter to Oscar Morland.
1975 - Spanish director J. A. Bayona is born.
1997 - Bree Moot 3 begins in Minneapolis.
2006 - A Tolkienian Mathomium is published.
2007 - Quest for Middle-earth is published.
2007 - Previews of The Lord of the Rings (musical) start in London.

content.title: In Arda
content.content: There are no known events for this day.
